 for bestpractices and # Dashboard

## Overview
You are building a comprehensive dashboard experience for the Investor Perception Platform (Gbox360). This MVP-focused dashboard serves as the primary authenticated landing area, surfacing a concise user snapshot: watched companies, recent Investor Perception Index (IPI) changes, alerts, and a quick company selector to accelerate navigation to in-depth IPI views or recent events. It must be robust, data-safe, and ready to extend with additional data sources. The implementation must guard against null/undefined values before using array methods, initialize React state appropriately, and validate API responses defensively.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- The Dashboard page is the authenticated landing hub for users. It provides at-a-glance visibility into:
  - Watched companies (with compact IPI spark and current change)
  - Recent IPI changes (timeline excerpts with directional indicators)
  - Alerts and system messages (non-intrusive bullets or cards)
  - Quick company selector (typeahead search) and time-window controls
  - Shortcuts to open the Company View (IPI Summary) for a selected company and time window, or to inspect recent events
- Goals:
  - Enable users to rapidly reach a company’s IPI view or inspect recent events
  - Provide a clean, premium fintech UI with clear typographic hierarchy and accessible controls
  - Integrate the Search & Filter component to facilitate discovery and drill-down
- Connected features:
  - Search & Filter: Typeahead company search plus filters for NarrativeEvents and IPI timelines
  - Company View (IPI Summary): Accessible via quick selectors; preview context on the dashboard
  - Email Verification: An intermediary page to verify email with tokenized links and reframing flows
- UI elements and visual guidance:
  - Top navigation bar: left-aligned logo, centered navigation links, right-aligned user controls (avatar, notifications, quick settings)
  - Watchlist panel: list of subscribed/watched companies with per-item tiny IPI spark indicators
  - Recent alerts panel: concise system messages with severity badges
  - Quick actions area: select company, set time window, replay/export actions
  - Main region: recommended company cards, brief IPI-change previews, and short blurbs for context
  - Typeahead search field integrated in the header for fast company lookup
- API integrations:
  - Data endpoints to fetch: watched companies, recent IPI changes, alerts, and lists of all companies for the typeahead
  - If real-time data is unavailable in MVP, provide mockable endpoints with deterministic mock data
  - No external APIs required by default; ensure the component gracefully handles empty/fallback data
- Visual guidance via design language:
  - Premium fintech aesthetic with a calm color story, serif display headings, sans-serif body text
  - Card-based layout with soft shadows, rounded corners, and responsive spacing
  - 12-column conceptual grid with a comfortable max content width to keep hero content centered and readable

## Components to Build
- DashboardShell
  - Layout: top navigation, left/right panels, responsive stacking
  - Safety: guards against null/undefined data; uses data ?? [] patterns for any array-like results
- WatchlistPanel
  - Props: watchedCompanies: arrays of { id, name, ticker, ipi, changeDirection, ... }
  - Behavior: render list with tiny IPI spark, click to navigate to Company View
  - Safety: validate arrays with Array.isArray before map
- IPIChangesPanel
  - Props: recentIp Changes: array of { companyId, ipiDelta, timestamp, narrativeSummary }
  - Behavior: compact timeline or sparkline per item
- AlertsPanel
  - Props: alerts: array of { id, level, message, timestamp }
  - Behavior: render list with visual severity cues
- QuickCompanySelector
  - Typeahead search field wired to a Company data source
  - Debounced input; suggestions dropdown; on selection navigate to Company View
- TimelinePreview
  - Displays short IPI timeline excerpt; optional “Why this move?” links
- CardsGrid
  - Reusable card component with consistent padding, radius, shadows
- FloatingPromoCard (optional)
  - Brown gradient, CTA emphasis for Learn More; sits in lower-right on large viewports
- CompanyViewLink
  - Utility button to navigate to Company View with selected company and window
- EmailVerificationLink
  - Reusable component for the Email Verification flow (on the separate page)
- DataVisualizationStub
  - Lightweight, non-blocking placeholder for future charts (follow neutral palette)

Technical details:
- All data access must guard against nullish results. Use patterns like:
  - const items = data ?? []
  - Array.isArray(data) ? data.map(...) : []
- Use proper TypeScript typings (where applicable) to enforce shape contracts
- Ensure components gracefully render when data is loading or absent

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Pages:
  - Dashboard.tsx (or equivalent) implementing the layout described
  - CompanyViewIPI.tsx (for the IPI Summary detail view)
  - EmailVerification.tsx (tokenized, status, and resending capability)
- Components:
  - Reusable UI primitives following the UI Component Kit (Buttons, Inputs, Cards, Tabs, etc.)
  - Typeahead component for quick company search with accessible ARIA attributes
  - Data cards with consistent typography, spacing, and shadows
  - Lightweight charts/graphs (optional) with minimal dependencies or pure CSS/SVG
- State management:
  - Use React useState and useEffect for local UI state
  - Use useMemo to derive derived data (e.g., filtered lists)
  - Ensure arrays are initialized with correct defaults: useState<T[]>([]) and avoid undefined
- Data handling:
  - Normalize any API response with defensive checks:
    - const watched = Array.isArray(response?.watched) ? response.watched : []
    - const ipiChanges = Array.isArray(response?.ipiChanges) ? response.ipiChanges : []
  - Implement null-safe map/filter/reduce as (items ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : []
- Accessibility:
  - All interactive controls have keyboard support and proper focus states
  - Color contrast checks with brand palette for readability
- Styling:
  - Implement styles using your preferred approach (CSS-in-JS, CSS modules, or plain CSS) following the provided design system
  - Ensure components respect the color tokens and typography guidelines
- Routing:
  - Provide routes for Dashboard, CompanyViewIPI, and EmailVerification
  - Navigation actions should pass necessary identifiers (companyId, window) via route params or state
- API layer (mockable by MVP):
  - Endpoints to support UI:
    - GET /api/dashboard (watched, ipiChanges, alerts, companies for typeahead)
    - GET /api/companies?query=... (typeahead suggestions)
    - GET /api/companies/:id/ipi?window=... (short IPI view)
    - POST /api/email/verify/resend (re-send verification)
  - Always guard response shapes:
    - const data = response?.data ?? []
    - const list = Array.isArray(data) ? data : []
- Security:
  - Ensure endpoints require authentication (simulate by adding isAuthenticated flag in mock)
  - Tokenized links for Email Verification should be non-sensitive in route (server should validate token)
- Validation:
  - Validate all inputs (typeahead query length, time window selection)
  - Prevent runtime errors when data is missing or malformed

### Backend
- APIs (as above) to support MVP dashboard
- Data model scaffolding (inferred):
  - User: id, email, emailVerified
  - Company: id, name, ticker
  - WatchedCompany: userId, companyId, settings
  - IPIChange: id, companyId, timestamp, ipiValue, narrativeSummary
  - NarrativeEvent: id, source, speaker, audience, text, timestamps
  - Alert: id, level, message, timestamp
  - RawEventPayload: id, companyId, payload, timestamp (audit trail)
- Functions:
  - fetchDashboardData(userId): composes watched, ipiChanges, alerts
  - searchCompanies(query): returns matching companies
  - fetchCompanyIPI(companyId, window): returns current IPI, delta, top narratives
  - resendVerificationEmail(userId): triggers email with tokenized link
- Data safety:
  - All responses should guard for nulls; return shapes consistent with frontend expectations
  - Persist raw payloads for auditing

### Integration
- Data flow:
  - Dashboard fetches data from /api/dashboard; front-end normalizes with defensive checks and populates WatchlistPanel, IPIChangesPanel, and AlertsPanel
  - Typeahead uses /api/companies to provide suggestions; on select, navigate to CompanyViewIPI
  - Quick actions trigger route changes to CompanyViewIPI with companyId and window
  - Company View page consumes /api/companies/:id/ipi to display IPIs and top narratives
  - Email Verification page uses /api/email/verify/resend for re-send flows and shows status via UI state
- State coherence:
  - Use consistent loading, error, and empty states
  - All array data should initialize to [] and guarded when rendering
  - Ensure useEffect dependencies are stable to avoid unnecessary re-renders

## User Experience Flow
- User lands on Dashboard:
  - Sees top navigation with a central set of links and a right-aligned user area
  - Typeahead search in the header ready to search companies
  - Watchlist shows a list of their watched companies with a tiny IPI spark and current value
  - Recent IPI changes appear as a compact timeline with directional arrows
  - Alerts area lists recent system messages with severity cues
  - Quick actions allow selecting a company and a time window, then either replay or export
  - Clicking a watched company or using the quick selector opens the Company View (IPI Summary) with relevant IPI data
- User drills down:
  - Typeahead helps locate a company quickly; selecting a result navigates to the detailed IPI view
  - On IPI Summary, the current IPI, change direction, top 3 narratives, and a concise event timeline are presented
  - Quick access to drill-down raw events is provided from the IPI Summary
- Email Verification flow:
  - User navigates to Email Verification page post-signup or when needed
  - The page shows verification status, tokenized link instructions, and a “Resend verification email” control
  - After verification, the user is redirected to the Dashboard or the next appropriate step

## Technical Specifications
- Data Models: 
  - User(id, email, emailVerified)
  - Company(id, name, ticker)
  - WatchedCompany(userId, companyId, createdAt)
  - IPIChange(id, companyId, timestamp, ipiValue, deltaDirection, narrativeSummary)
  - NarrativeEvent(id, source, speaker, audienceClass, rawText, timestamp)
  - Alert(id, level, message, timestamp)
  - RawEventPayload(id, companyId, payload, timestamp)
- API Endpoints:
  - GET /api/dashboard?userId=... -> { watched: [], ipiChanges: [], alerts: [], ... }
  - GET /api/companies?query=... -> [{ id, name, ticker }]
  - GET /api/companies/:id/ipi?window=... -> { currentIpi, change, topNarratives: [] }
  - POST /api/email/verify/resend -> { status: 'sent' | 'error' }
- Security:
  - All dashboard data endpoints require user authentication
  - Email verification uses secure tokenized links; verification endpoint validates token
- Validation:
  - Defensive checks for response shapes; use Array.isArray and data ?? [] for arrays
  - Validate inputs (query length, windows) with sensible defaults
  - Use optional chaining for nested API fields

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Dashboard renders with sections: Watchlist, IPI changes, Alerts, and Quick Company Selector
- [ ] All arrays are handled safely without runtime errors: use (items ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray checks
- [ ] useState hooks for arrays/objects are initialized with correct types: useState<SomeType[]>([]) and useState<SomeType | null>(null) only where appropriate
- [ ] Typeahead provides at least 5 suggestions for a non-empty query and gracefully handles empty results
- [ ] Clicking a watched company or a typeahead result navigates to Company View (IPI Summary) with correct context
- [ ] Company View displays current IPI, directional change, top 3 narratives, and a simple timeline
- [ ] Email Verification page shows status, ability to resend verification email, and tokenized link handling
- [ ] All API responses are validated before rendering; default to empty arrays or safe defaults when missing
- [ ] UI adheres to the provided design system, color tokens, typography, and spacing rules
- [ ] Frontend runtime safety rules are enforced in all data handling paths

## UI/UX Guidelines
Apply the project's design system:
- Color Palette tokens as defined in Visual Style
- Typography: serif display for headings, sans-serif body; ensure strong hierarchy
- Card surfaces with 16–20px radii and soft shadows
- Navigation: white header with centered links and right-aligned actions
- Interactive states: hover/focus lift, subtle shadows, and color depth
- Layout: generous left/right padding, centered content with max width ~900–1000px for hero; 12-column grid conceptually

## Visual Style

### Color Palette:
- Primary Green: #2f6f63
- Secondary Teal/Gray-Teal: #2b6250
- Neutral White: #ffffff
- Page Background Taupe: #a79e96
- Hero Beige: #f3efe6
