1. Supabase query results: Always use nullish coalescing — const items = data ?? []
2. Array methods: Never call on a value that could be null/undefined. Use (items ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : []
3. React useState for arrays/objects: Initialize with correct type — useState<Type[]>([])
4. API response shapes: Always validate — const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
5. Optional chaining: Use obj?.property?.nested when accessing nested API data
6. Destructuring with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}

PROJECT CONTEXT NOTES
- TARGET PAGE: Dashboard (as described)
- Sprint 1 MVP: End-to-end MVP MVP with data ingestion, Typeahead, IPI, and drill-down
- No external API dependencies necessary for MVP; structure endpoints to be mockable
- The UI must be production-ready with runtime safety at the forefront

Deliverables
- A complete, actionable implementation prompt that an AI development tool can execute to build the Dashboard, Company View, and Email Verification pages, including frontend components, backend API endpoints, data models, and integration wiring, all with the required runtime safety guarantees.

